job description:
We are Domosapiens- uniquely skilled, passionate data lovers anchored in a culture of connectivity. We are transforming the way business is managed by putting real-time data into the hands of every decision-maker across organizations. Diversity is valued here because homogenized teams create echo chambers; and nobody benefits from that. The insight garnered from diverse backgrounds, perspectives, and lived experiences results in pioneering innovations across the organization and better experiences for our customers. The more diverse our talent, the more impactful the Domosphere becomes.

Position Summary

Data Scientists on Domo's Data Science Professional Services Team are client-facing experts who work with Domo's strategic clients on custom production data science use cases and associated business solutions. This role requires data scientists to understand and demonstrate competence in four knowledge domains: data engineering, model building, customer and initiative management, and problem-solving. These four domains apply to all aspects of building a production data science pipeline in Domo—including use case discovery, ROI estimation and tracking, data ingestion, data preparation and cleaning, feature engineering, modeling, training, and building out technical and end-user dashboards.

As a customer-facing data scientist, work time is balanced between calls and on-site interactions with Domo clients, with independent time allocated to building custom, production-ready data science solutions for clients. Furthermore, data scientists on this team are teachers and trainers, with a firm emphasis on evangelizing data science best practices and enabling customers to understand and own their Domo data science solutions. They also use and promote the data science suite of tools that are available in the Domo platform.

Data Scientists are also contributors to Domo's Data Science Center of Excellence (COE). Through the COE, data scientists are encouraged to pursue innovative projects that enhance clients' user experience and move forward the vision of data science at Domo. This can include contributing to the building of Domo data science products, designing and architecting apps, writing knowledge base articles, developing sales and marketing solutions, or contributing to Domo-sponsored published works.

At the senior level, data scientists are expected to demonstrate expert knowledge and industry respect and longevity in at least two of the four knowledge domains (data engineering, model building, customer and initiative management, and problem-solving).

Key Responsibilities
Accurately scope data science initiatives and gather requirements from clients;
Execute all phases of a client-facing production data science initiative;
Successfully manage a portfolio of data science client projects;
Teach and train customers on data science best practices and production data science solutions;
Develop innovation initiatives that support and enhance the Domo product.
Job Requirements
University degree or equivalent industry experience with an emphasis in data science, statistics, behavior science, computer science, or related field;
Strong R and/or Python skills (5+ years);
Knowledge and demonstrated application of a breadth of statistical and data science approaches;
Portfolio of at least one completed data science and/or statistics project, including visualizations, presentations, reports, etc. (such as a class project, etc.);
Experience in any type of customer-facing role (2+ years);
Strong written and verbal communication skills;
Detail-oriented;
Exceptional time management skills.
Nice to have
Master's Degree or Ph.D. with an emphasis in data science, statistics, behavior science, computer science, or related field;
Portfolio of independently completed data science and/or statistics projects, including visualizations, presentations, reports, etc. (industry-specific portfolio preferred);
Experience teaching statistics and/or data science, with evidence of success (such as favorable course evaluations, etc.);
Project management experience;
Experience using Domo (1+ years).
Domo is an equal opportunity employer.

ABOUT POWER FACTORS

Power Factors is a leading provider of asset performance management solutions through our cloud-based SaaS Drive platform. Drive empowers owners, operators and asset managers with tools to effectively manage a fleet of clean energy assets for real-time operations, reporting and technical asset management.

THE ROLE

As a Data Scientist on the Power Factors’ Advanced Analytics team, you will serve as an in-house subject matter expert on solar, storage and Power Factors’ Drive platform. In this role you will support internal and external users, conduct analysis that exceeds the current capability of the product and help define and validate the road map for future development.

You will work closely with a wide variety of internal teams (Product Management, Customer Success, Software Development, Engineering Operations and, obviously, other members of Advanced Analytics) as well as customers (Analysts, Site Managers and Asset Managers). You will have the opportunity and responsibility for communicating with experts from across the industry. Extensive knowledge of solar, and operational solar power plants is, therefore, a must. Familiarity with analysis, data science and software development tools and techniques are preferred.

The best candidates will have strong written and verbal communication skills, be curious and willing to continually take on new challenges and opportunities to learn (new programming languages, techniques, technologies). In this role, you will be reporting to the Technical Director of Advanced Analytics and you will be an active member of a team composed of passionate and highly qualified professionals that aims at changing the energy landscape.

IMPORTANT NOTE: Power Factors is applying COVID-19 preventive measures to safeguard the health and safety of our employees, customers, business partners, and communities where we have offices. Please note that the selected candidate will be working from home, for the duration of said applicable measures.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Serve as an internal expert for the inner workings of all aspects of Power Factor’s Drive platform;
Understand customer needs and use cases and how they can be addressed;
Support testing, documentation, training, utilization and value realization of the platform;
Help define workflow and user experience elements of the platform;
Collaborate with other members of the Advanced Analytics team to explore analytical problems and solutions;
Work independently to investigate and develop analytical methods and tools;
Communicate effectively with people at all levels of the organization and with customers;
Ensure that analytics are robust and resilient in a production environment with diverse data;
Work with Data Engineers on data quality assessment, data cleansing and analytics;
Collaborate with Product Managers to understand requirements and use cases;
Develop, verify and validate analytics to address customer needs and requirements;
Continuously strive to efficiently deliver actionable information to Power Factors’ customers. You will interact directly with internal and external stakeholders to design solutions that help them solve real-world problems and drive value.
Work on a multitude of dynamic projects with cross-functional internal stakeholders as required.

REQUIREMENTS

Bachelor’s degree (or above) in Engineering, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, or a related field;
Minimum 3 years of relevant work experience in Solar and / or Energy Storage; practical experience with monitoring and analysis of operational generating assets is considered as an asset;
Minimum of 3 years of experience with data analysis and / or data science strongly preferred;
Experience with data analysis tools (e.g. Python, SQL, PowerBI preferred);
Demonstrated experience with development and deployment of analytical methods and tools using IoT data;
Ability to grasp and clearly communicate complex ideas;
Commercially oriented approach and business skills in identifying and exploiting opportunities in a competitive market;
Demonstrated skill at data preprocessing, data modeling and data quality assessment (especially as related to IoT data);
Ability to continuously learn and explore new techniques to provide insights and answers;
Critical thinking and problem-solving skills;
Experience developing analytics for product solutions is also considered an asset;
Availability to travel on occasions or as required (10% of the time approximately).

WHAT WE OFFER

A highly motivated, values-driven culture focused on a sustainable energy future
Flexible core hours
Incentive pay and employee referral bonus programs
Employee recognition programs
Benefits coverage for you and your dependents

REQUIRED COMPETENCIES

Accountability
Delivering on Commitments
Customer Focus
Problem Analysis
Process Development
Problem Solving

EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER

Power Factors is an Equal Opportunity Employer committed to engaging a diverse workforce and sustaining an inclusive culture. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or veteran status.

